<sec id="id-d677134b-a55d-4c07-ba0a-1ef33c9e79fc"><title><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="eb886704-ffaf-499b-9aac-77ea8d3a998c" timestamp="1627506858251"?>Rules governing individual identity(ies), authentication, recognition, and use<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="eb886704-ffaf-499b-9aac-77ea8d3a998c"?></title><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="e83548d7-9f17-4dfd-8e57-fa559cf397fc" timestamp="1627506880660"?>Learning transactions differ in their nature and goals. The rules governing a learning transaction, (a) may allow a Person to use one of several Person identities, (e.g., one of several different credit cards or passports); or, (b) require a Person to have/use a pre-specified Person identity (e.g. a Blue Cross card, a national health insurance card, a student identity card, etc.).<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="e83548d7-9f17-4dfd-8e57-fa559cf397fc"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="09dd91b2-f8ef-4b6c-e2b8-f950476de118" timestamp="1627506880660"?><bold>Rule 056:</bold><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="09dd91b2-f8ef-4b6c-e2b8-f950476de118"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="ac458b48-d255-45d6-f9cd-2a294567b4fa" timestamp="1627506880660"?><bold>The individual identity, i.e., the persona and the associated identifier, used by an individual in a learning transaction, shall be capable of being prescribed depending on the context and goal of the learning transaction.</bold><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="ac458b48-d255-45d6-f9cd-2a294567b4fa"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="763f4822-d173-441c-b8cc-85254d6c79d4" timestamp="1627791860580"?>Based on the rules in Clause<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="763f4822-d173-441c-b8cc-85254d6c79d4"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="6861742" change-id="d0890ec8-d9f7-4a3f-928f-a6a473745dee" timestamp="1633269758540"?>s<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="d0890ec8-d9f7-4a3f-928f-a6a473745dee"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="ad9858b3-af4d-4c37-b170-05eecaebd1ea" timestamp="1627791860580"?> <xref as:rid="chunks/82851/id-2d733b42-d791-4f4a-8e30-b13be1dde87f.xml#id-1476e007-3a10-404c-d916-90755526a7d8" ref-type="sec" id="id-b866179e-93ba-463a-d876-850e571ac187" xmlns:as="http://niso-sts-authoring-solution/authoring-schema"><?fontoxml-text-placeholder text="type the link text"?></xref> and <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="ad9858b3-af4d-4c37-b170-05eecaebd1ea"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="6861742" change-id="f13c46f4-47c2-4405-8b21-93f86f8c2a13" timestamp="1633269815611"?>8.4 <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="f13c46f4-47c2-4405-8b21-93f86f8c2a13"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="6861742" change-id="46b21e30-382f-4634-d521-a994c7993b1b" text=" " timestamp="1633269812600"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="97a67671-af11-4e31-f3e0-508da72bdf4c" timestamp="1627791860580"?>above, and drawing on elements in <xref as:rid="chunks/82851/id-ee8491e6-54c1-4a4d-9cd0-afacb6b757d0.xml#id-6c37232f-2958-4121-c828-eeaa4566538c" ref-type="fig" id="id-b83fa583-df08-46c7-9bd2-ce3a0442093f" xmlns:as="http://niso-sts-authoring-solution/authoring-schema"><?fontoxml-text-placeholder text="type the link text"?></xref>, <xref as:rid="chunks/82851/id-b7a6d642-24bf-49a4-ba7f-100238582955.xml#id-6ad4bf47-b02a-475c-b34e-fcc767cbb775" ref-type="fig" id="id-7edc1d74-8dea-4b7f-f73b-9b86b33cdab4" xmlns:as="http://niso-sts-authoring-solution/authoring-schema"><?fontoxml-text-placeholder text="type the link text"?></xref><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="97a67671-af11-4e31-f3e0-508da72bdf4c"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="6861742" change-id="743db747-4479-419c-d7aa-bd5acb1d373c" timestamp="1633269751604"?> <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="743db747-4479-419c-d7aa-bd5acb1d373c"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="cec00d29-7ebc-44f1-a278-125816110f97" timestamp="1627791860580"?>illustrates the range of one-to-one bindings between the personae and identifiers of an individual as</p><p>individual identities (ii) defined as:<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="cec00d29-7ebc-44f1-a278-125816110f97"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="6e8e693f-4300-40a2-b781-f3d38898ad2d" timestamp="1627506880660"?><bold><italic>individual identity</italic></bold><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="6e8e693f-4300-40a2-b781-f3d38898ad2d"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="85499b51-b8ca-466c-f10c-14c75a76a40e" timestamp="1627506880660"?><bold><italic>ii</italic></bold><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="85499b51-b8ca-466c-f10c-14c75a76a40e"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="5066bbc1-9168-42d3-9f0c-14357b24dc92" timestamp="1627506880660"?><bold><italic>Person identity</italic></bold> <italic>of an <bold>individual,</bold> i.e. an individual identity, consisting of the combination of the <bold>persona</bold> information and <bold>identifier</bold> used by an <bold>individual</bold> in a <bold>learning transaction</bold>, i.e. the making of any kind of <bold>commitment</bold></italic><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="5066bbc1-9168-42d3-9f0c-14357b24dc92"?></p><non-normative-note><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="0f9a8fe7-899e-493b-ca75-995b2f32df61" timestamp="1627791493142"?><bold><italic>Adapted from ISOIEC 15944-8, 3.059.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="0f9a8fe7-899e-493b-ca75-995b2f32df61"?></italic></bold></p></non-normative-note><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="507138dc-ba5a-4217-f1be-5482b3ba640d" timestamp="1627791495126"?></p><fig id="id-6ad4bf47-b02a-475c-b34e-fcc767cbb775" specific-use="size:M"><caption><title>Illustration of range of links between personae and identifiers of an individual identity (ies) of a learner</title></caption><graphic xlink:href="images/82851/7" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/></fig><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="507138dc-ba5a-4217-f1be-5482b3ba640d"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="edc71c31-2e1c-46c7-f749-0d88924d953a" timestamp="1627506880660"?><bold>Rule 058:</bold><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="edc71c31-2e1c-46c7-f749-0d88924d953a"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="6f833932-3475-4908-b23c-51228d37671d" timestamp="1627506880660"?><bold>A specific individual identity (ii) established by a registration authority, i.e., organization or public administration, should not be used for any purpose other than that for which it was created, unless with the express and explicit consent of the individual.</bold><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="6f833932-3475-4908-b23c-51228d37671d"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="6f0adb83-6647-4f4f-eb4e-d4ce5859ecae" timestamp="1627506880660"?><bold><italic>Guideline 058G1:</italic></bold><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="6f0adb83-6647-4f4f-eb4e-d4ce5859ecae"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="03c4e2da-b021-40f3-b147-81ca09f5658a" timestamp="1627506880660"?><bold><italic>A recognized individual identity (rii) based on a Registration Schema (RS) of Registration Authority (RA) has the added attribute of being re-useable and thus is the preferred approach in support of Open-edi.</italic></bold><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="03c4e2da-b021-40f3-b147-81ca09f5658a"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="e3e1b4b9-e0b9-4efd-c734-a4d3e85a1312" timestamp="1627506880660"?>A individual identity which is recognized for use in a learning transaction is known as a “recognized individual identity” and is defined based on the existing Part 1 definition of for the concept of “recognized person identity” (rPi)” which has been adapted as follows:<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="e3e1b4b9-e0b9-4efd-c734-a4d3e85a1312"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="0e64648d-594b-4903-f557-8130bf0486e2" timestamp="1627506880659"?><bold><italic>recognized individual identity</italic></bold><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="0e64648d-594b-4903-f557-8130bf0486e2"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="f11d063b-1c57-479a-d00e-e9b54e747268" timestamp="1627506880659"?><bold><italic>rii</italic></bold><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="f11d063b-1c57-479a-d00e-e9b54e747268"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="c43c7926-10c9-4676-c355-52f9d319b7c7" timestamp="1627506880659"?><italic>identity of an <bold>individual,</bold> i.e., <bold>individual identity</bold>, established to the extent necessary for the specific purpose of a <bold>learning transaction</bold></italic><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="c43c7926-10c9-4676-c355-52f9d319b7c7"?></p><non-normative-note><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="3aa77907-3ca5-484c-f0c5-7f1b2e724de4" timestamp="1627774507153"?><italic>Adapted from ISO/IEC 15944-8:2012, 3.118.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="3aa77907-3ca5-484c-f0c5-7f1b2e724de4"?></italic></p></non-normative-note><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="02d382c8-ee99-4f9c-aa00-7230b31bd101" timestamp="1627506880659"?>When a Person identity is presented for use in a learning transaction, it has to be “recognized” by the other parties to the learning transaction. Each party to the transaction may have its own rules governing the requirements for establishing a “recognized Person identity (rPi).<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="02d382c8-ee99-4f9c-aa00-7230b31bd101"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="f5bb7a5b-cee5-4cbd-9de4-bd6555b871a9" timestamp="1627506880659"?>Applying the existing ISO/IEC 15944-1 rules governing identification and authentication of Person to an individual learner based on applicable common external constraints, i.e., those stated in Clause 5 above is illustrated in Figure H.8. It is an adaptation of Figure 12 in Clause 6.2.3 of ISO/IEC 15944-1.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="f5bb7a5b-cee5-4cbd-9de4-bd6555b871a9"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="feb665da-608d-4303-a64d-a6f11c427191" timestamp="1627506880659"?>Given the fact that persona Registration Schema (RS), of a Registration Authority (RA),<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="feb665da-608d-4303-a64d-a6f11c427191"?></p><list list-type="order"><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="5f03793d-ce0d-4762-f9d5-91adab761c64" timestamp="1627506880658"?><list-item id="id-68d8e9ff-4b51-4e9e-c26c-fe4e1cbc5019"><p>may or may not, include the registration of individuals; and,</p></list-item><list-item id="id-5a9c2093-103b-402e-f9f7-745d3735e698"><p>if the RS, does allow for the registration of individuals as members, then external constraints of a privacy protection requirements nature apply,</p></list-item><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="5f03793d-ce0d-4762-f9d5-91adab761c64"?></list><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="f73786ff-188b-4035-edcf-aa104db37884" timestamp="1627506880658"?>it is necessary that one distinguish between a pRS which does not contain individuals as members and those which does, in whole or in part, i.e., as individual persona Registration Schema (ipRS).<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="f73786ff-188b-4035-edcf-aa104db37884"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="a79ce090-903c-40fc-9164-286d3ea9efc8" timestamp="1627506880658"?><bold>Rule 059:</bold><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="a79ce090-903c-40fc-9164-286d3ea9efc8"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="4352f1c8-69c2-4532-85d3-7f253bbf9127" timestamp="1627506880658"?><bold>For any persona Registration Schema which includes, in whole or in part, individuals as members, external constraints of a privacy protection nature apply and all its registrants which are individuals shall be managed as members of an individual persona Registration Schema (ipRS) in accordance with applicable privacy protection requirements.</bold><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="4352f1c8-69c2-4532-85d3-7f253bbf9127"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="e78f8fb5-f58c-41bb-906a-61d77dd24b28" timestamp="1627506880658"?>Expanding the definition for the concept of “persona Registration Schema (pRS), an “individual persona Registration Schema (ipRS)” is defined as follows:<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="e78f8fb5-f58c-41bb-906a-61d77dd24b28"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="a434d53d-79d4-4dbe-f0c9-0634b9babbff" timestamp="1627506880658"?><bold><italic>individual persona Registration Schema</italic></bold><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="a434d53d-79d4-4dbe-f0c9-0634b9babbff"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="3895c48b-7740-4fcc-f0c4-e7e346846666" timestamp="1627506880658"?><bold><italic>ipRS</italic></bold><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="3895c48b-7740-4fcc-f0c4-e7e346846666"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="6dfd0a6c-6344-4ae6-b195-5a8c18502433" timestamp="1627506880657"?><bold><italic>persona Registration Schema (pRS)</italic></bold> <italic>where the <bold>persona</bold> is, or includes, that of an <bold>individual</bold> being registered</italic><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="6dfd0a6c-6344-4ae6-b195-5a8c18502433"?></p><non-normative-note><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="f7b0c2c2-c1a0-4411-db65-d30db4508f8c" timestamp="1627774486678"?><italic>Where an persona Registration Schema includes persona of sub-types of Persons, i.e., individuals, organizations, and/or, public administrations, those which pertain to individuals shall be identified as such because public policy as external constraints apply including those of a privacy protection requirements nature.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="f7b0c2c2-c1a0-4411-db65-d30db4508f8c"?></italic></p></non-normative-note><non-normative-note><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="8fbf9fed-645d-4016-e07f-8ab89eb7ea03" timestamp="1627774407773"?><italic>In a individual persona Registration Schema, one shall state whether or not a truncated name, i.e. registered persona, of the individual, is allowed or mandatory, and if so the ipRS shall explicitly state the rules governing the formation of the same.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="8fbf9fed-645d-4016-e07f-8ab89eb7ea03"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="7671038" change-id="2351c1bb-bce6-4437-b3cd-1cf983e8b9d2" text="The ISO/IEC 7501 multipart standard re “Machine Readable Travel documents”, (e.g. passports) as well as, the ISO/IEC multipart 7812 “Identification cards” standard also do this." timestamp="1644575808260"?></italic><xref ref-type="fn" as:rid="chunks/82851/id-b7a6d642-24bf-49a4-ba7f-100238582955.xml#id-d27b102c-5122-4105-87d3-7d6f6277c08e" id="id-3919547c-35c9-49ab-9955-3c2f9ef7bb6f" xmlns:as="http://niso-sts-authoring-solution/authoring-schema"><?fontoxml-text-placeholder text="type the link text"?></xref><fn id="id-d27b102c-5122-4105-87d3-7d6f6277c08e"><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="7671038" change-id="57616be4-223b-4a0c-e887-54390c285b47" timestamp="1644575820647"?>The ISO/IEC 7501 multipart standard re “Machine Readable Travel documents”, (e.g. passports) as well as, the ISO/IEC multipart 7812 “Identification cards” standard also do this.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="57616be4-223b-4a0c-e887-54390c285b47"?></p></fn></p></non-normative-note><non-normative-note><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="7a66ee1b-cc5b-4756-ef2a-1679f7251ad4" timestamp="1627774419247"?>[ISO/IEC 15944-8, 3.060]<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="7a66ee1b-cc5b-4756-ef2a-1679f7251ad4"?></p></non-normative-note><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="4691883c-0df5-44ef-d70b-bc847ccb37c6" timestamp="1627506880657"?>The selection of an individual identity in a learning transaction between the LET provider and the individual learner as one which is recognized for use between them (as well as any other parties to that learning transaction) is basically established in one of two ways:<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="4691883c-0df5-44ef-d70b-bc847ccb37c6"?></p><list list-type="order"><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="fb63ffac-08fb-4e22-9b7f-59ec5e7fd6f4" timestamp="1627506880657"?><list-item id="id-3227d896-e1e4-4bff-957c-410a3655ca66"><p>the individual identity to be recognized (and accepted) for use in a learning transaction is one that is established and mutually agreed to between the buyer and the individual. It is thus a “mutually defined - recognized individual identity (md-rii)”.</p></list-item><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="fb63ffac-08fb-4e22-9b7f-59ec5e7fd6f4"?></list><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="14b747e5-8fca-41ef-b91c-8f9b65ce61c6" timestamp="1627506880657"?>Use of such a “md-rii” is found in learning transaction involving internal constraints only. Quite often they are of a one time nature only and not “re-useable”. As such, even though the use of a “md-rii” can be modelled in an Open-edi scenario as a scenario component, information bundle, and/or semantic component, it does not have the generally property of re-usability and thus is not a preferred approach in Open-edi.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="14b747e5-8fca-41ef-b91c-8f9b65ce61c6"?></p><list list-type="order"><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="e9036ade-3579-41f3-ae83-54648983ace0" timestamp="1627506880656"?><list-item id="id-d280cea1-d6cc-469e-c02d-4a7628c4125e"><p>the individual identity to be recognized (and accepted) for use in a learning transaction where the buyer is an individual is one based on that established through a Registration Schema (RS) of a Registration Authority. It is thus a “<underline>Registration Schema (based) –recognized individual identity” (RS-rii”)</underline>.</p></list-item><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="e9036ade-3579-41f3-ae83-54648983ace0"?></list><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="5e80d992-a41c-4457-d948-37c1ba1d006d" timestamp="1627506880656"?>The need be able to support these two basic approaches a recognized identity is supported by two relevant concepts, which are defined as follows:<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="5e80d992-a41c-4457-d948-37c1ba1d006d"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="23d42b78-7523-4e0e-ea45-2565d6dcd83c" timestamp="1627506880656"?><bold><italic>mutually defined - recognized individual identity</italic></bold><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="23d42b78-7523-4e0e-ea45-2565d6dcd83c"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="6d2ad0d0-c657-43c0-c8ff-1944aa4e9ebb" timestamp="1627506880656"?><bold><italic>md-rii</italic></bold><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="6d2ad0d0-c657-43c0-c8ff-1944aa4e9ebb"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="814f6468-99c9-44aa-f75d-cb967f7428b7" timestamp="1627506880656"?><bold><italic>recognized individual identity (rii)</italic></bold> <italic>which is mutually defined and agreed to for use between the <bold>LET provider</bold> and the <bold>individual learner,</bold> as <bold>buyer,</bold> in a <bold>learning transaction</bold></italic><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="814f6468-99c9-44aa-f75d-cb967f7428b7"?></p><non-normative-note><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="480b2c82-f6c2-4421-a525-bdd8f8c78cb1" timestamp="1627774316752"?>The establishment of a mutually agreed to and recognized individual between a LEET provider and individual learner, as buyer, does not extinguish the applicable privacy protection rights of that individual.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="480b2c82-f6c2-4421-a525-bdd8f8c78cb1"?></p></non-normative-note><non-normative-note><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="856c68f8-a91d-4719-d134-8bf1df16145e" timestamp="1627774359849"?>A mutually defined recognized individual identity (md-rii) shall be established between the LET provider and the individual learner no later than the end of the negotiation phase.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="856c68f8-a91d-4719-d134-8bf1df16145e"?></p></non-normative-note><non-normative-note><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="09872fb2-949d-4f08-ebec-30cb51bf5f83" timestamp="1627774371059"?>Use of a mutually defined recognized individual identity (md-rii) may not be permitted where external constraints apply.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="09872fb2-949d-4f08-ebec-30cb51bf5f83"?></p></non-normative-note><non-normative-note><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="f62ed4b0-3964-4f5d-e5d6-912b31e7f56c" timestamp="1627774383651"?>Adapted from ISO/IEC 15944-8, 3.080.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="f62ed4b0-3964-4f5d-e5d6-912b31e7f56c"?></p></non-normative-note><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="91267d7f-8365-48ec-9315-2d2f6c21c82f" timestamp="1627506880655"?><bold><italic>Registration Schema (based) –recognized individual identity</italic></bold><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="91267d7f-8365-48ec-9315-2d2f6c21c82f"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="99887f43-b611-4db8-fe8e-b38706fa61d2" timestamp="1627506880655"?><bold><italic>RS-rii</italic></bold></p><p><bold><italic>recognized individual identity (rii)</italic></bold> <italic>for use in a <bold>learning transaction</bold>, by the buyer as an <bold>individual</bold>, which is one based on the use by an <bold>individual</bold> as a member of a specified <bold>Registration Schema (RS)</bold> of a particular <bold>Registration Authority (RA)</bold></italic><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="99887f43-b611-4db8-fe8e-b38706fa61d2"?></p><non-normative-note><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="c798a8da-844e-4056-cb44-770d17bb0105" timestamp="1627774304035"?>Adapted from ISO/IEC 15944-8, 3.127<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="c798a8da-844e-4056-cb44-770d17bb0105"?></p></non-normative-note><fig id="id-88189e91-6f53-463c-8914-f2bc3d27c55f" specific-use="size:M"><caption><title><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="402ef3b0-f5a2-498b-f87e-66d0193e3eb3" timestamp="1627791702986"?>Illustration of two basic options for establishment of a recognized individual identity (rii)<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="402ef3b0-f5a2-498b-f87e-66d0193e3eb3"?></title></caption><graphic xlink:href="images/82851/8" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/></fig><p/><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="baddcd47-3339-4008-84cb-d392e8593d1c" timestamp="1627506880655"?><bold>Rule 060:</bold><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="baddcd47-3339-4008-84cb-d392e8593d1c"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="9ca50c9c-46ae-423f-ddde-055940de45f7" timestamp="1627506880654"?><bold>A Registration Authority (RA) for individuals shall have explicitly stated rules for transforming an individual identity into a recognized individual identity to meet a stated business requirement.</bold><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="9ca50c9c-46ae-423f-ddde-055940de45f7"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="25dc294c-a328-443f-c47e-73df2598400e" timestamp="1627506880654"?><bold>Rule 061:</bold><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="25dc294c-a328-443f-c47e-73df2598400e"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="8fd3da8c-6e10-417e-b589-1701eb689843" timestamp="1627506880654"?><bold>The rules governing a learning transaction may either require the use of a specified recognized individual identity (rii) or allow for several of a similar nature.</bold><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="8fd3da8c-6e10-417e-b589-1701eb689843"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="e74ae64c-23ac-4454-9e6e-83152e7bbdc8" timestamp="1627506880654"?>For example, if payment by credit or debit card is allowed in a learning transaction, several different brands of cards may be allowed, but not necessarily all. It can also happen that for specific learning transactions, an individual may be required to present a “legally” recognized individual identity such as a births certificate, passport, a driver’s license, a landed immigrant card, etc.<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="e74ae64c-23ac-4454-9e6e-83152e7bbdc8"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="64a0146f-a7d3-4074-e408-61938d3473ef" timestamp="1627506880654"?>The establishment or verification of a recognized individual identity will require the capability for authentication, i.e., individual authentication, especially in (electronic) learning transaction. As such individual authentication is defined as:<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="64a0146f-a7d3-4074-e408-61938d3473ef"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="a6a4577d-0940-425f-a0f7-1c722c2b4f85" timestamp="1627506880654"?><bold><italic>individual authentication</italic></bold><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="a6a4577d-0940-425f-a0f7-1c722c2b4f85"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="ed65c8a4-185c-4696-d8e7-b086c5faf869" timestamp="1627774284859"?><bold><italic>provision</italic></bold> <italic>of the assurance of a <bold>recognized individual identity (rii)</bold> sufficient for the purpose of the <bold>learning transaction</bold></italic></p><non-normative-note><p>Adapted from ISO/IEC 15944-8:2012, 3.058.</p></non-normative-note><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="ed65c8a4-185c-4696-d8e7-b086c5faf869"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="7808926b-c06a-4155-9624-562075fc7d59" timestamp="1627506880653"?>For individual authentication to be successful, the following actions must have taken place:<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="7808926b-c06a-4155-9624-562075fc7d59"?></p><list list-type="order"><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="2717ea80-f68d-4e09-9391-0c551ce8a0ce" timestamp="1627506880653"?><list-item id="id-e693fd4f-d522-4799-fbcc-2c1a6fa523d4"><p>the individual identity must have been established; and,</p></list-item><list-item id="id-85e4fe4b-65ed-46af-ce52-25589fc69366"><p>the individual identity must be recognized, i.e. a recognized individual identity (rii), must exist.</p></list-item><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="2717ea80-f68d-4e09-9391-0c551ce8a0ce"?></list><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="89bca256-3668-4c18-8e69-55831ed6c33e" timestamp="1627506880653"?><bold>Rule 062:</bold><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="89bca256-3668-4c18-8e69-55831ed6c33e"?></p><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="adea9527-aea7-4163-80c1-a40a31d51a06" timestamp="1627506880653"?><bold>In a learning transaction, individual authentication is established by either:</bold><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="adea9527-aea7-4163-80c1-a40a31d51a06"?></p><list list-type="order"><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="andres@nii.ac.jp" change-id="a014bd15-a4be-4efa-f46f-89272784237c" timestamp="1627774189660"?><list-item id="id-a3e2cb2b-89ed-4373-c6e1-69a0be71252a"><p><bold>mutual definition and acceptance: or,</bold></p></list-item><list-item id="id-7d6ba493-ba71-4e0f-af42-7835a333ca59"><p><bold>referring to predefined individual persona registration schema (ipRS) and process of a particular RA.</bold></p></list-item><?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="a014bd15-a4be-4efa-f46f-89272784237c"?></list><p/></sec>
